[1] Cholera - Zambia
Date: Thu, 23 Feb 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: TodayOnline [edited]
<http://www.todayonline.com/articles/102593.asp>

More than 130 people have died of cholera in Zambia since the disease
broke out in August 2005, the health minister revealed.
"So far, we have recorded 137 deaths and over 5000 have been treated
and discharged from the cholera centers," Sylvia Masebo said Wed, 22
Feb 2006. She said the government was struggling to contain the
deadly water-borne disease because of an increase in informal housing
and a lack of proper sanitation.
More than 100 people are currently being treated at centers set up to
deal with the disease.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
